f he/she is 4 levels below or above me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/01 11:59:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class do you Fear the most in PvP?</span><hr size=1> Agree with Cylant.  Anyone faster than myself.<br><br>If, I had to pick one, it'd be Necromancers.  Lifetap and pets.  Used to be druids and mages before I got my MR up and could afford to burn thru pumice stones. <p>Majestyk, <a href="http://Server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Rogue</a>, <a href="http://www.talonguard.org/shanks">Shanks</a>, <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5034">Vallon Zek!</a>We as Shanks, have chosen the hard path. In the hardness of it, is where we find the glory.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ularlanalavode.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Larlana Lavode</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/01 7:36:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class do you Fear the most in PvP?</span><hr size=1> For myself, used to be bards, but now that they can be rooted or ensnared, NOT any more, hehehe.<br><br>But I would say a paladin or a shadow knight are probably the two to fear the most.  If the SK gets you down far enough, his HT will kill you.  On the other hand, if the Paladin gets his Lay on Hands in there, we are toast due to being down SO many hit points from the start.  I thought I had an even con Paladin really screwed up when I layed into him with Muscle Lock, but with him him healing himself, and then getting the Lay on Hands in there, I knew I had to run because of getting hit with a Weighted Axe.  NOT a nice thing to face if they know how to use it correctly.<br><br><br>Larlana Lavode<br>Mistress of Assassins<br>The Wraithguard<br>Tallon Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/01 8:00:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class do you Fear the most in PvP?</span><hr size=1> necromancers are int casters, and have low AC, therefore.. unless there is some ungodly intervention.. they won't be able to cast.  This of course only holds true if i'm jumping them.. the opening darkness dosn't stick.. or it's a duel.  If the battle starts by me being jumped with a darkness.. i'm dead.. =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvilian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vilian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/01 11:17:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What class do you Fear the most in PvP?</span><hr size=1>     shadow knights ...soo i make it my goal to kill them or aleast attempt to ...at every chance meeting<br><br> my record is getting better....but not good enough <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> Vilian Of Vallon  DLB <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uproztorvalds.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Proz Torvalds</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/16/01 8:31:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> without a doubt Druids and SK's. Both are damn scary 50+. <br><br>/pet attack<br>click winged death hotkey<br>run around in circles<br>dead rogue<br>/cry<br><br><br><br>/discipline smolderingpileofroguegooenhancer<br>click smolderingpileofroguegoo hotkey<br>dead rogue<br> /cry.<br><br><br>-Allundra Landstalker <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ularlanalavode.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Larlana Lavode</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/16/01 2:54:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> True, there have been enough complaints about Winged Death as it seems to be just UNGODLY in PvP, and from what it sounds like, is not &quot;nerfed&quot; for PvP with the amount of damage it does.  I also hear that it is a bugged spell that can't always be cured.  But personally, I don't fear druids much.  If I'm able to get on them, they are generally running for their lives, and a blind druid is a scared druid.<br><br><br>Larlana Lavode<br>Mistress of Assassins<br>The Wraithguard<br>Tallon Zek <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwiergraf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wiergraf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/16/01 7:25:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=107.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Personally, I have a fear of druids. Melees are laughable if trying to PK someone, hybrids are a bit tougher, especially SKs with Harmtouch, but druids just scare me.<br><br>I recently hit high enough with MR that I almost never am rooted, but they still just frighten me. Whenever I die to a PK, it's usually to a dr00d casting snare with SoW on, some DoT, and then running around casting fire spells.<br><br>On the other hand, if it's in the Arena, I can waste druids because they can't kite me very well in such an enclosed space as the platform. <p><br><br>Wiergraf Deathstalker<br>Proud Member of the Shadow Gypsies<br><i>Thinking? Who said anything about thinking? Kill first, then loot.. thinking is that unpleasant shouting business when it all has to be divided up. It makes brains hurt.</i>--Torm the Thief</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubikbuz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bikbuz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/paris/5799/dance.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Register